metatags.og:title: This is a UNICEF photo of a Moroccan child, not a former French education minister
metatags.og:description: A collage of two photographs – one of a young shepherd girl and another of France's first female education minister – has been shared hundreds of times in multiple Facebook and Twitter posts alongside a claim that they show the same person. The claim is false; the first photo shows a young Moroccan girl called Fouzia who was featured in a UNICEF report in 2015; the second photo shows Najat Vallaud-Belkacem, France's education minister from 2014 until 2017.

metatags.og:description: A collage of two photographs apparently depicting the struggle story of French politician Najat Vallaud-Belkacem is going viral on social media. The post claims that a young girl shepherd from Morocco grew up to be France’s education minister 20 years later. India Today’s Anti Fake News War Room (AFWA) has found that the young girl in the first photograph is not Najat Vallaud-Belkacem.
